interestingcomments.content:
Cleaned my Nikon d7100 sensor, and now it's worse. /!/ I used sensor swabs and solution, one wet pass and one dry pass, with a rocket blower. I cleaned a lens as control and took a shot at f/16 close against a white wall to see if the specks were gone; they weren't. I completed the cleaning and testing process two more times. Now not only are the original spots still there, but there are more specks now. I'm thinking about taking it into a shop. I need my camera for a shoot and I'm just getting frustrated.
Any alternate methods or ideas?
